  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Global Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated legal enforcement\n- Cross-border investigation mechanisms\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory and legal standards.",
